      "amount": "1/2 tsp"
    },
    {
      "name": "Extra Virgin Olive Oil",
      "amount": "3 tbsp"
    },
    {
      "name": "Salt",
      "amount": "to taste"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C).",
    "Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add crumbled tofu and cook for about 2 minutes.",
    "Add finely chopped onions, garlic, thyme, oregano, black pepper, red chili flakes, and salt. Stir-fry until the onion is translucent, approximately 3-4 minutes.",
    "Increase heat to high, add sliced rhubarb, and continue cooking until the rhubarb begins to brown, about 5 minutes.",
    "Reduce heat to medium-low and stir in tomato paste, letting it simmer for a minute. Adjust seasoning as needed.",
    "Serve hot over quinoa or rice for added protein and nutrition."
